        "text": "The Nidiaci Community Garden is managed by the local community, with limited interference by institutions.\nAn important feature is that, apart from being a playground, use of the area depends on what people decide to put into it, for free. For example:\n- We host the only self-managed football school in town, where children learn to enjoy playing and not\nonly winning,\n- a British writer teaches English,\n- a Portuguese musician teaches the violin,\n‚Ä¢ the families organise markets to share children's clothes for free and avoid waste,\n‚Ä¢ we organise a small community garden,\n‚Ä¢ we are working on monitoring pollution and traffic using equipment provided by the National\nResearch Council,\n‚Ä¢ and much else."
