        "id": "97e434dda843d33a",
        "text": "It is called a \"garden,\" but it is way more: a community meeting space, neighborhood gathering spot, playground, soccer camp, place for music lessons, and green oasis in the busy city center of Florence, [[Italy]]. Nidiaci Community Garden is not managed by city agencies, but is stewarded by the parents of the Oltrarno neighborhood, who manage this rare garden for children."
